AI PODCAST GENERATOR — DEPLOYMENT GUIDE
========================================
Mobile PWA version (GitHub Pages + Cloudflare Workers)


FILES IN THIS PACKAGE
=====================

  podcast-generator.html   The app
  manifest.json            PWA manifest (makes it installable on Android)
  sw.js                    Service worker (required for install prompt)
  icons/icon-192.png       App icon
  icons/icon-512.png       App icon (large)
  worker.js                Cloudflare Worker code (paste into Cloudflare dashboard)
  DEPLOY.txt               This file


STEP 1 — DEPLOY THE CLOUDFLARE WORKER
======================================
This is your secure proxy to the Claude API. No credit card required.

1.  Go to https://cloudflare.com and create a free account (email only)

2.  In the dashboard, click Workers & Pages in the left sidebar

3.  Click Create → Create Worker

4.  Delete the default "Hello World" code entirely

5.  Open worker.js from this package and paste the entire contents

6.  Click Deploy — Cloudflare gives you a URL like:
        https://your-worker-name.your-account.workers.dev
    Note this URL down — you'll need it later.

7.  Go to your Worker → Settings → Variables and Secrets

8.  Click Add Secret:
        Name:  ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
        Value: your Claude API key (sk-ant-...)
    Click Save

9.  Click Add Secret again:
        Name:  APP_PASSWORD
        Value: a password you choose (e.g. "BlueFox92!" — anything memorable)
    Click Save

    Your API key and password are now encrypted and will never be visible again.

10. Test your Worker by visiting:
        https://your-worker-name.workers.dev/claude
    You should see: {"error":"Not found"} — this means it's running correctly.
    (It returns an error because you need to POST with the right headers, not GET)


STEP 2 — PUBLISH TO GITHUB PAGES
===================================

1.  Go to github.com and create a new repository
    Name it something like: podcast-generator
    Set it to Public (GitHub Pages requires this on free accounts)
    Tick "Add a README file"
    Click Create repository

2.  Upload these files to the repository root:
        podcast-generator.html
        manifest.json
        sw.js
        icons/icon-192.png
        icons/icon-512.png

    To upload: click Add file → Upload files, drag them all in, commit.

3.  Enable GitHub Pages:
    Go to repository Settings → Pages
    Source: Deploy from a branch
    Branch: main  /  (root)
    Click Save

4.  Wait about 60 seconds, then your app is live at:
        https://yourusername.github.io/podcast-generator/podcast-generator.html

    GitHub will show the URL in Settings → Pages once it's ready.


STEP 3 — UPDATE GOOGLE OAUTH FOR YOUR GITHUB PAGES URL
========================================================
Your existing OAuth Client ID needs the GitHub Pages URL added to it.

1.  Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
2.  Click your existing OAuth client to edit it
3.  Under Authorised JavaScript origins, click + Add URI:
        https://yourusername.github.io
4.  Under Authorised redirect URIs, click + Add URI:
        https://yourusername.github.io/podcast-generator/podcast-generator.html
5.  Click Save

Note: keep your existing localhost entries if you still want the desktop
version to work. You can have multiple origins and redirect URIs.


STEP 4 — CONFIGURE THE APP
============================
Open your GitHub Pages URL in Chrome on your phone (or desktop).

Fill in the fields:
  - Claude API key: your sk-ant-... key
  - App password: the password you set in Cloudflare (Step 1, item 9)
  - Worker URL: https://your-worker-name.workers.dev/claude
    (your Cloudflare Worker URL with /claude at the end)
  - OAuth Client ID: your existing Client ID

Tick "Remember on this device" for each — you only need to enter them once
per device.

Click Connect Google Drive and sign in.


STEP 5 — INSTALL AS AN APP ON ANDROID
=======================================
1.  Open Chrome on your Android phone
2.  Visit your GitHub Pages URL
3.  Chrome will show a banner at the bottom: "Add Podcast Gen to Home screen"
    Tap Install (or Add)
4.  The app icon appears on your home screen
5.  Tap it — it opens full screen like a native app

If the banner doesn't appear automatically:
- Tap the three-dot menu in Chrome → "Add to Home screen"


USING BOTH DESKTOP AND MOBILE
===============================
The desktop version (start.cmd + proxy.py) continues to work exactly as
before — nothing changes there.

The mobile/PWA version uses the Cloudflare Worker instead of the local proxy.
Both versions share the same Google Drive account and upload files to the
same place — so you can generate on desktop or phone interchangeably.


SECURITY SUMMARY
=================
- Your Claude API key is stored as an encrypted Cloudflare secret
  (never in code, never visible after saving)
- The APP_PASSWORD prevents anyone else from using your Worker even if
  they find your GitHub Pages URL
- OAuth tokens are stored in localStorage on your device only
- The GitHub repository contains no secrets — it's safe to be public
- Worst case if your Worker URL leaks: someone would need both the URL
  AND your APP_PASSWORD to make API calls


TROUBLESHOOTING
================
"Invalid password" error
  → The APP_PASSWORD in the app doesn't match the secret in Cloudflare.
    Double-check both. Passwords are case-sensitive.

"Worker error 404"
  → Make sure your Worker URL ends in /claude
    e.g. https://my-worker.workers.dev/claude  (not just /workers.dev)

"Worker error 500"
  → The ANTHROPIC_API_KEY secret may be wrong or missing in Cloudflare.
    Go to Worker → Settings → Variables and Secrets and check.

Drive shows "Not connected" on phone
  → The silent re-auth only works if you're signed into Google in Chrome.
    Tap Connect Google Drive to re-authenticate.

"redirect_uri_mismatch" when connecting Drive
  → Add your GitHub Pages URL to the OAuth client's Authorised redirect
    URIs (Step 3 above). Wait a few minutes for Google to propagate.

Install prompt doesn't appear on Android
  → The PWA requires HTTPS (GitHub Pages provides this automatically).
    Make sure you're visiting the https:// URL, not http://.
    Try Chrome menu → Add to Home screen if the banner doesn't show.

App icon appears but shows blank screen
  → Hard-refresh: in Chrome tap menu → Reload. If still blank, clear
    Chrome's cache for the site in Settings → Site settings.
